    name: 'Lipid-Lowering Drugs',
    slug: 'lipid-lowering-drugs',
    description: 'Statins, ezetimibe, PCSK9 inhibitors, fibrates, niacin',
    content: {
      concept: \`# Lipid-Lowering Drugs

## Classification

| Class | Examples | Primary Effect |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| **Statins** | Atorvastatin, Rosuvastatin | ↓↓ LDL |
| **Ezetimibe** | - | ↓ LDL (cholesterol absorption) |
| **PCSK9 inhibitors** | Evolocumab, Alirocumab | ↓↓↓ LDL |
| **Fibrates** | Fenofibrate, Gemfibrozil | ↓↓ TG, ↑ HDL |
| **Niacin** | - | ↑↑ HDL, ↓ TG |
| **Bile acid sequestrants** | Cholestyramine | ↓ LDL |
| **Omega-3 fatty acids** | Icosapent ethyl | ↓ TG |
| **Bempedoic acid** | - | ↓ LDL (ACL inhibitor) |

---

## STATINS (HMG-CoA Reductase Inhibitors)

### Mechanism
\`\`\`
Statins inhibit HMG-CoA reductase →
  ↓ Cholesterol synthesis →
  ↑ LDL receptor expression →
  ↓ Plasma LDL (20-55%)

Also: ↓ TG, ↑ HDL slightly
Pleiotropic effects: Anti-inflammatory, plaque stabilization
\`\`\`

### Potency Ranking
High-intensity (↓ LDL >50%):
- Atorvastatin 40-80 mg
- Rosuvastatin 20-40 mg

Moderate-intensity (↓ LDL 30-50%):
- Atorvastatin 10-20 mg
- Rosuvastatin 5-10 mg
- Simvastatin 20-40 mg

### Adverse Effects
| ADR | Mechanism | Notes |
|-----|-----------|-------|
| **Myopathy** | ↓ Ubiquinone (CoQ10) | 5-10% muscle symptoms |
| **Rhabdomyolysis** | Severe myotoxicity | Rare, ↑ with fibrates |
| **Hepatotoxicity** | Idiosyncratic | Check LFTs baseline |
| **New-onset DM** | Unclear | Higher with potent statins |

### Drug Interactions
- CYP3A4 substrates (atorvastatin, simvastatin) - grapefruit, azoles, macrolides
- Gemfibrozil + Statin = High rhabdomyolysis risk (avoid simvastatin)

---

## EZETIMIBE

### Mechanism
Blocks NPC1L1 transporter in intestine → ↓ Cholesterol absorption → ↓ LDL 15-20%

### Use
- Add to statin for additional LDL lowering
- Statin-intolerant patients

---

## PCSK9 INHIBITORS

### Drugs
- Evolocumab, Alirocumab (monoclonal antibodies)
- Inclisiran (siRNA - twice yearly)

### Mechanism
PCSK9 degrades LDL receptors → Blocking PCSK9 → ↑ LDL receptors → ↓↓ LDL (50-60%)

### Use
- Familial hypercholesterolemia
- ASCVD with inadequate LDL control on max statin

---

## FIBRATES

### Mechanism
PPAR-α agonists → ↑ Lipoprotein lipase → ↓↓ TG (30-50%), ↑ HDL

### ADRs
- Myopathy (especially with statins)
- Gallstones
- GI upset

---

## TREATMENT APPROACH

\`\`\`
Primary prevention (high risk) → Moderate-intensity statin
Secondary prevention (ASCVD) → High-intensity statin ± ezetimibe
LDL still high → Add PCSK9 inhibitor
High TG (>500) → Fibrate (prevent pancreatitis)
\`\`\`\`,
      keyPoints: [
        'Statins: HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors, most effective for LDL reduction',
        'High-intensity: Atorvastatin 40-80 mg, Rosuvastatin 20-40 mg',
        'Statin ADRs: Myopathy, hepatotoxicity, new-onset diabetes',
        'Ezetimibe: Blocks intestinal cholesterol absorption, add to statin',
        'PCSK9 inhibitors: For familial hypercholesterolemia, ↓ LDL 50-60%',
        'Fibrates: PPAR-α agonists, primarily ↓ TG',
        'Gemfibrozil + simvastatin: Avoid (high rhabdomyolysis risk)'
      ],
